    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-25T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-25T03:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.86A/8–2554: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 364<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Saudi Arabia (<persName corresp="#p_WG1"
                            type="from">Wadsworth</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d364fn1">Repeated to Dhahran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-25T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 25, 1954—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. Further my telegram 72, August 23.<note n="2" xml:id="d364fn2">Not printed.
                        (886A.2553/8–2354)</note> Was received yesterday by King for general review
                    US-Saudi relations. His attitude extremely <pb facs="0893" n="853"
                        xml:id="pg_853"/> cordial; will appoint commission work out details modified
                    five year army program; asked me discuss Saudi membership <gloss
                        target="#t_IBRD1">IBRD</gloss> with Prince <persName corresp="#p_IAAF1"
                        >Faisal</persName>; made appointment see <persName corresp="#p_DFA1"
                        >Davies</persName> re Onassis’ agreement.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DFA1">Davies</persName> saw him late yesterday; discussion
                    cordial;… representatives <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> will meet today.</p>
                <p>Still later Defense Minister saw Colonels Boyd and <persName corresp="#p_MCRD1"
                        >McCarten</persName>; said King wished them get down to work at once;
                    offered fullest cooperation.</p>
                <p>My feeling is tide our relations has turned but am wondering whether it is not
                    rather because of other developments (e.g. Gholam Mohammad’s and <persName
                        corresp="#p_NCGA1">Nasir</persName>’s advice and shift Egyptian policy
                    following Suez agreement) than as result persuasion our part.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
